reviews.text: Waited 40 minutes for our food. They seemed extremely under-staffed, so I can let that slide. However, I don't think the food was worth the wait. Honestly, Domino's is better in my opinion. There was also an occasional bad smell around the back of the restaurant.  I'm not sure if it was the men's restroom or someone who was sitting in that area, but it smelled a bit like sewage... Don't think I'll ever be back.
My husband and I each had a calzone. They looked and smelt wonderful. They were delicious. I recommend eating here if you looking for good pizza.

Unfortunately, this is the second pizza order that I was missing items and also incorrect.  I was told by a manager, I was to receive a gift card for the 1st incorrect order (bone in wings with no sauce instead of boneless and mild sauce and missing 2 sauces)that i never recieved. Now this is the second order within a month, missing sauces, pizza has the wrong sauce and my pizza was undercooked.  Just disappointed, we will be looking for a new pizza place. In a positive, it was a fast delivery time.

Ordered delivery tonight.. first they brought the wrong order. Then he brought correct order and dropped it in the front yard. When I called and spoke to manager all she said was ... Ya he called me and we are making another one.. like .. I've been waiting to eat for two hours now . My husband got cold wings and I got the worst taco salad I've ever had

detailedReviews.author: Lindy Schmidt
detailedReviews.text: Unfortunately, I am forced into writing this review. Last October, we ordered take out from Bruno's. When we opened the boxes at home, we found that our cheese pizza had hardly any cheese. The taco pizza had only hamburger on it. That's it. No cheese, no chips, lettuce... The fries tasted like they were fried in old oil. Not a great experience. And the worst part was that we had ordered because we had company in town. When I went back to Bruno's to discuss this issue, I told them I would rather hash it out in person, than write a bad review. The manager was thankful, and said she would have corporate send me a gift certificate for the amount of my order, but it would take up to 6 weeks. That time came and went; I called, and they assured me it was still on the way. Well, here it is, 7 months later, and still nothing. I'm not giving this up, but I can for sure say we won't be eating there anymore. And I'd warn you away from take out too.

detailedReviews.author: D Yahneezy
detailedReviews.text:
Giving Bruno's 2 stars pains me because they used to be the only place we went to for our pizza, but lately I've noticed the service and quality of food has declined so I thought I'd share. Our last visit was pretty bad and management doesn't seem to care after we wrote in to them requesting response (there hasn't been one).

We ordered take out and ended up getting someone else's food, which we didn't realize till we got back home. Not a problem at all, so right away we call it in to be told that they had noticed something was wrong! Kinda weird they said that, but not a problem, these things happen so I ask to have our order fixed and was told they would send it out quick and should arrive in 25.

A couple more calls back and an hour and a half later, the correct pizza finally arrives lukewarm. Apparently the driver had other orders to deliver, and I'm betting we were the last priority. We were told twice that the order was on its way and we felt lied to. We didn't even get to keep the other pizza at the end of all this. We still tipped the driver too, cuz it probably wasn't his fault, but wishing we hadn't after the pizza was barely warm.

Do yourself a favor and just go somewhere else.

They didn‚Äôt check on us once after they dropped off the pizza to see how it was going but to just drop off the check. We also ordered 2 beers and a seltzer on tap either their 2-4-1 deal and they were all flat as could be, even the seltzers. customerMoodAnalysis.sentimentSummary: Customer opinions are divided. The 3.5/5 rating from 100 recent reviews suggests some great experiences mixed with areas needing attention.

strengthsPerceived: Customers love the delicious and unique pizza options, including gluten-free choices, which are a treat for visitors. - social media marketing can showcase this strength
The restaurant consistently offers a 30% off code, which customers appreciate and remember. - Boostly marketing services can amplify this
The friendly staff and enjoyable dining experience make it a favorite place to eat, whether dining in or ordering out. - review management can highlight this positive aspect
improvementOpportunities: Long wait times and incorrect orders - Boostly marketing services can improve this
Negative reviews and reputation issues - review management can address this concern
